\c 21
\s1 An old man called Ahimelek helped David
\p 
\v 1 \w After|strong="H6965"\w* \w that|strong="H5892"\w*, David \w went|strong="H3212"\w* \w to|strong="H3212"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* place called Nob. \w There|strong="H6965"\w* \w was|strong="H5892"\w* \w an|strong="H6965"\w* old man \w there|strong="H6965"\w* called Ahimelek. \w He|strong="H3212"\w* used \w to|strong="H3212"\w* look \w after|strong="H6965"\w* God’s ceremonies. \w He|strong="H3212"\w* saw David coming \w with|strong="H3212"\w* \w no|strong="H6965"\w* soldiers. \w There|strong="H6965"\w* \w were|strong="H5892"\w* just \w a|strong="H3068"\w* few work-men \w with|strong="H3212"\w* \w him|strong="H3083"\w*. \w This|strong="H6965"\w* \w made|strong="H3083"\w* Ahimelek afraid. \w He|strong="H3212"\w* \w was|strong="H5892"\w* \w so|strong="H6965"\w* frightened \w that|strong="H5892"\w* \w he|strong="H3212"\w* shook. \w He|strong="H3212"\w* asked David, “Why did \w you|strong="H6965"\w* \w come|strong="H3212"\w* here \w all|strong="H3212"\w* \w by|strong="H6965"\w* yourself? Where \w are|strong="H5892"\w* \w your|strong="H6965"\w* soldiers? What happened?”
